# Skill rules

Skills are reusable capabilities stored as SKILL.md folders under `skills/`. They are
the **how**; the agents are the **who**. Roles invoke skills; skills do not invoke each
other. Skills load by progressive disclosure: name + description always visible, body
only when needed, heavy resources only when used. This is how the team stays capable
without burning context tokens.

## Sourcing order (do not reinvent)
Before building reusable logic:
1. Scan the skills registry (`skills/README.md`).
2. Check the curated upstream **addyosmani/agent-skills** and pull a matching skill if
   one exists (copy it in, keep attribution).
3. Check `@nathanokh/codebase`.
4. Only if nothing fits, have the Skill Smith author a new skill from `_template`.

## Loading
Do not load all skills at once — it wastes context. Load only the skills relevant to
the current phase (see the phase->skill->role table in `skills/README.md`).

## Descriptions are triggers
A skill's `description` must state BOTH what it does AND when to use it, leaning
slightly pushy so it fires when relevant. Do not summarize the workflow steps into the
description, or the agent may follow the summary instead of reading the full skill.

## Promotion
After building something reusable inline, flag it as a promotion candidate so the Skill
Smith lifts it into a proper skill and registers it.
